transcription.text:
Speaker 1: Thank you for calling Viagra. My name is Jessie. May I get your first and last name?

Speaker 2: My first name is Jim.

Speaker 1: And your last name?

Speaker 2: Wasil. W-A-S-I-L.

Speaker 1: Perfect. Mr. Wasil, what's your zip code?

Speaker 2: 32940.

Speaker 1: Thank you. Are you at 1277 Cypress Trace Drive in Melbourne, Florida?

Speaker 2: That's me.

Speaker 1: Okie dokie. And then let's see here.

Speaker 2: What can I help you with?

Speaker 1: I got my first prescription yesterday, but I'm not sure that it's the right thing,

Speaker 2: because on the bottle it just says, you know, it's generic for Viagra.

Speaker 1: Let me take a quick look. The best way to know is, do you have the pills there with you,

Speaker 2: like the actual bottle?

Speaker 1: I do.

Speaker 2: Okay. If you can take out one of the pills, you'll see it's smooth on one side,

Speaker 1: and on the other side there's an imprint.

Speaker 2: Can you tell me the imprint, because that will inform me of who the manufacturer is.

Speaker 1: Okay. It's AC-340.

Speaker 2: No, that's wrong. Okay, so that's the American AGV.

Speaker 1: I want to get you the French ones.

Speaker 2: The correct pill, or the French pill, the French AGV, will have a stamp of 100,

Speaker 1: and that's how you know it's the correct one.

Speaker 2: I didn't think this was the right pill, so what do I do about it?

Speaker 1: Yeah. Oh, don't worry. We're going to replace it. We'll replace it for you.

Speaker 2: We'll have it expedited. At no cost to you, obviously, because you've already been here.

Speaker 1: Yeah, not the greatest for my very first experience.

Speaker 2: Yeah, very sorry about that. We'll go ahead and have that shipped out to you.

Speaker 1: And with that one, you're welcome to try it. It's American-made.

Speaker 2: If you like it, then keep it. You get double the pills at this point.

Speaker 1: But otherwise, we're still sending you the AGV.

Speaker 2: Those are not made in China or India. Those are made in the USA.

Speaker 1: Okay. So this is not the – let me see. Let's see. Hang on one second.

Speaker 2: Okay. Let's see.

Speaker 1: Yeah, it's supposed to be the – what kind of – it's some different Viagra.

Speaker 2: What's the number or something?

Speaker 1: It's the AGV. So the AGV is a new pill. It's made in France. It's FDA-approved.

Speaker 2: Just bear in mind, though, before I let you go, you know, at first blush,

Speaker 1: it might look similar. They're not. Okay? So the stamp on the AGV will have 100.

Speaker 2: The only other pill that has 100 is the branded blue Viagra.

Speaker 1: That indicates the manufacturer.

Speaker 2: Number two, the bottle will actually read AGV on it.

Speaker 1: And number three, the pharmaceutical located on the side of the bottle

Speaker 2: where the label is will read Greenstone. Greenstone is a subsidiary of Pfizer. Okay?

Speaker 1: Okay. Got it all.

Speaker 2: Awesome. Okay. Thank you so much. Bye-bye.
